summary: Comprehensive testing of Analytics Logs Tab with individual log entries and per-row delete functionality. All backend tests (14/14) and frontend tests passed. The Analytics tab is visible in project detail page with Scripts, Embed, Analytics tabs. The table shows Source URL, Link Script, Status, Requests, Last Access, and Action columns. Each row has a functional delete button that removes the specific log entry and updates the summary stats.

issues: Minor: React console warning about span inside tbody - does not affect functionality

passed_tests: Backend: GET /api/projects/{id}/analytics/logs returns 200
Backend: Response has summary stats (total, allowed, denied)
Backend: Response returns individual log entries array
Backend: Log entry has required fields (id, referer_url, script_url, script_name, status, requests, last_access)
Backend: Log entry status is 'allowed' or 'denied'
Backend: Log entry ID is integer (for delete operations)
Backend: DELETE /api/projects/{id}/logs/{log_id} deletes specific log entry
Backend: DELETE non-existent log returns 404
Backend: DELETE log from wrong project returns 404
Backend: Summary stats update correctly after delete
Backend: script_url format is /api/js/{project_slug}/{script_slug}.js
Backend: limit parameter works for limiting returned logs
Backend: Authentication required for GET analytics/logs
Backend: Authentication required for DELETE log
Frontend: Analytics tab visible in project detail page
Frontend: Three tabs present: Scripts, Embed, Analytics
Frontend: Summary stats cards show Total Requests, Allowed, Denied
Frontend: Access Logs table shows all 6 columns: Source URL, Link Script, Status, Requests, Last Access, Action
Frontend: Source URL is clickable link (blue, underlined)
Frontend: Link Script is clickable link (blue, underlined)
Frontend: Each table row has delete button (trash icon)
Frontend: Delete button removes log entry when clicked
Frontend: Summary stats update after deletion
Frontend: Success toast 'Log entry deleted' shown after delete
Frontend: Empty state shown when no logs exist
critical_code_review_comments: AnalyticsLogsTab component correctly implements individual log entry display with per-row delete
Backend endpoint GET /api/projects/{id}/analytics/logs returns flat list of log entries with IDs
Backend endpoint DELETE /api/projects/{id}/logs/{log_id} correctly deletes single log entry
Frontend properly updates local state after delete without full page reload
logsAPI.delete and analyticsAPI.getLogs functions properly integrated in api.js
All interactive elements have proper data-testid attributes (analytics-tab, analytics-logs-section, analytics-logs-table, log-row-{id}, delete-log-{id})
seed_data_creation: Test projects with scripts and access logs created dynamically during pytest tests with TEST_ prefix. Automatically cleaned up after test completion.
